article.headline: Houston 83, East Carolina 59
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Robert McKiver scored 23 points to lead Houston to an 83-59 win over East Carolina on Saturday night. Jahmar Thorpe scored 15 points and Dion Dowell added 11 for the Cougars (13-10, 7-3 Conference USA). Oliver Lafayette grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds. Darrell Jenkins scored a game-high 31 points for East Carolina, which had no other players in double figures. Jenkins made 10 of his 13 shots, including eight of 10 from beyond the 3-point line to score more than half of East Carolina's points. Gabe Blair led the Pirates with seven boards, but he did not score any points in the game. The Pirates (5-18, 0-10) shot 37 percent from the field and were outrebounded 42-23. Houston led 44-20 at halftime.
